description:
Looking like aliens from another world, the SAS troopers stormed through a deadly cocktail of phosphorous smoke and CS gas. With them was Yuri Muravyev, once a sergeant in the Spetsnaz - the elite Soviet shock force - now an advisor to their UK equivalent.And the SAS were out to prove that they were every bit as tough as their Russian counterparts - with the north of England as their unlikely battleground!

By: Mike Knowles
name: Shock Force U.K.! Yuri Strikes Back

description:
In the scorching heat of the desert, the German Panzer troops have clear orders to destroy a British artillery unit standing in their way.The gunners are holding out against the onslaught, but Sergeant Bill Mercer reckons it's only a matter of time before the order will be given for a fighting retreat.Bill is determined to keep his men alive at all costs - and if that means going head to head with his newly-appointed superior officer, so be it...

By: Ferg Handley
name: "Smash Those Guns!"

description:
The 17th Century was a time of strife in Great Britain as the forces of Parliament fought the supporters of the King for supremacy.Two friends, young farmers Tam Nicol and Jock Mackie, found themselves battling to defend their village in the Scottish Highlands. It would take all of their cunning and courage to survive this brutal civil war!

By: Ferg Handley
name: Civil War - Blood and Honour

description:
Every man there had broken a rule, spoken out of turn to some important official or simply been in the wrong place at the wrong time. Now they were all expendable, sent to a squadron with obsolete equipment and detailed to battle where the action was thickest and deadliest.The other thing they had in common was that they could fight. Boy could they fight! The Germans learned this to their cost... and so did at least one of the men who had sent them there...

By: Norman Adams
name: Convict Squadron

description:
There's deep snow on the ground, feet thick in places, too deep to walk through. So how would you rescue three hostages from a powerful, well-armed group of mercenaries from whose isolated base you could hear any force coming miles away.Ask Captain Kevin Cook of the SAS or Lieutenant Neil Blake of the Royal Marine Commandos, they know. If you're lucky, they'll tell you how they mounted the silent strike.

By: Alan Hebden
name: The Silent Strike

description:
Fifteen-year-old lads like Otto Hartmann and very elderly veterans like Walther Werner were typical of the men who made up the rank and file of the VolksSturm , Germany's Home Guard.With little training and even less hope, they were throw into battle and expected to hold back the relentless tide of Allied armour as the Third Reich crumbled all around them...

By: Ian Clark
name: Cellar Rats

description:
Bill and Johnny King were twins, but Bill was always that much better at any sport you cared to mention. So Johnny learned to live in his brother's shadow. The same thing happened when war threatened. Both were dead keen to fly, but it was Bill who qualified as a pilot while Johnny was ruled out on medical grounds.Yes, Bill was certainly destined for glory, but it was what Johnny could do one dangerous day which would decide which of the twins would survive... if either!

By: Bernard Gregg
name: Second Best?

description:
Harry "Dutch" Holland was prepared to admit that the 25-pounder was a good gun. But Harry had spent his early Army days on the North-West Frontier of India and, to him, no gun could better the old 3.7 inch screw howitzer, designed specifically for use in those hostile mountains.And as the Second World War raged, Harry was delighted to get his hands on a screw gun again. He'd show his mates and the enemy alike just what a punch the semi-obsolete gun packed!

By: Alan Hemus
name: Harry's Gun

description:
The orders were simple - trek five miles into the depths of enemy territory, scale a vertical cliff face by dead of night... then hit an enemy stronghold.It sounded an impossible task, but it was just another mission for the elite shock troops of the Soviet Union - the Spetsnaz!

By: Mike Knowles
name: Shock Force

description:
Lieutenant Frank Naylor of the Special Operations Executive was determined to do well on his first field operation - helping French freedom fighters set up a resistance network in the coastal region of Brittany.However, with a hot-headed French sergeant to keep in line and a possible traitor in their midst, Frank's first mission might well turn out to be his last...

By: Ferg Handley
name: Battleground Brittany

description:
In 1936, Hans Leibner was drafted into the Wehrmacht. The young German disliked the Nazis and all they stood for, though, so he deserted and made for Spain. The country was in the midst of a brutal civil war between the Nazi-backed Fascist Nationalists and freedom-fighting Republicans. Hans joined an International Brigade - a group of foreign volunteer soldiers dedicated to fighting for the Republican cause.It was a deadly business with many casualties, and things would get even worse when Hans was suspected to be an enemy agent...

By: Ferg Handley
name: Storm Over Spain

description: Trev Walker of the East London Light Infantry liked to spin a yarn. Stuck on a troopship waiting to sail for the Normandy beaches, he had the opportunity... and a captive audience.He began to tell a story, a tale so strange that his fellow soldier's didn't know whether to believe it or not.So was it true? You'll have to decide for yourself.
name: Dead Man's Boots

description: A big day for the Royal Air Force. Fly with a Hawker Typhoon close-support squadron into deadly danger over the Normandy beaches...
name: Close Support!

description: A big day for the Royal Navy above and below the waves. Follow the crew of a midget sub into deadly danger close to the Normandy beaches...
name: To Lead the Way

description: A big day for the British Army and all the soldiers involved. Follow the crew of a Sherman Firefly tank into the deadly danger of the Normandy beaches...
name: Beach-head Battle

description: A big day for British Commando Robbie Sinclair. Follow him every step of the way from his training in the Scottish Highlands to where he now stands stripped to the waist on a French dockside, armed only with his Commando knife against the bullets whistling around him.Robbie wasn't born a hero. To tell the truth, he was a good bit scared. But he knew that part of the success of the D-Day invasion would depend on what he did in the next thirty seconds. That was when he really began to earn the proud name "Commando"!
name: D-Day Plus

description: Sergeant Steve Havers was a member of the Parachute Regiment, a Para. He was as tough as they come. But he had an Achilles' heel - fire! His morbid fear of flames could stop him in his tracks.And on his D-Day drop, any hesitation would cost him his life.
name: Fight Fire with Fire

description: D-Day +25. Lieutenant Len Harper's Commando unit were dead beat. They'd been right at the sharp end since the Allies set foot in Normandy. They were due a rest - but they got another mission instead.And no easy mission, either. Would any of them survive the jailbreak?
name: The Jailbreak

description: Sergeant Matt Jackson, a veteran Commando, found himself in a German Stalag - the only survivor of the ambush that had wiped out his squad. Though he hated being behind the wire, there seemed little he could do.Then he and his fellow inmates - British and Russian - were forced by their ruthless German captors to help build a deadly supergun.Matt decided it was time to fight back...
name: Prison Break!
Fast Gun
Jinx Pilot

description: It was a small sculpture, the bronze statue of a lion. Made to celebrate a famous victory, it was later lost after an infamous defeat.Now, centuries later, it was at the heart of a battle once again. Two different groups of soldiers wanted it. Two groups who needed to fight as allies, not enemies, if they were to survive.
name: Battle of the Lion

description: When Germany surrendered in 1945, Lieutenant Harry Bryson, a British submariner, was a prisoner of the Japanese. Oberleutnant Mac Haggmeir, a U-Boat commander, was delivering supplies to the Far East at the same time and he realised that the fanatical Japanese badly wanted his U-Boat.It was a mad scheme to get out of this nasty situation that would bring Harry and Max together as a pair of very unlikely allies.
name: Strange Allies

description: Through the centuries the McCranes had been fighting men, their muscle and strength winning many a clan battle.In the Second World War, Jamie McCrane joined up to do his bit. But Jamie was different from his ferocious forebears - he used his brain as well as his brawn to win his victories!
name: Warrior Tradition

description: The death of Peter Lacy's father had seemed like an open-and-shut case at the time. "Careless handling of a shotgun", was the official verdict.Peter was soon to learn, though, that it had been no accident. It was cold-blooded murder carried out on the command of a bunch of fanatics.Who were these sinister killers? And why did they now want Peter to join their brotherhood of evil?
name: Brotherhood of Evil

description: A clash between big, lumbering bombers was strange enough - dog-fighting was usually left to the fighter escorts. But what made this giant duel doubly odd was that, only weeks before, these Italian Savoia-Merchetti SM79s and their crews had belonged to the same squadron!
name: Giant Duel

description: German Bernhardt Boldt and Piet De Groot from Holland. Hydrofoil boat commanders, the two had been at each other's throats since 1940.Now, five years later, the end was in sight. Not just of the war but of their blood feud.It was time for a final battle, and there could only be one winner - a duel to the death!
name: H-boat versus H-boat

description: Greece, 1941 and a British squad find themselves without transport in a wild, dangerous area. Then they happen upon an abandoned motorcycle and all clamber aboard in an attempt to get back to their lines. Along the way they pick up an escaping Italian colonel and end up with Germans and Greek partisans on their trail.Six men. One bike. And a whole lot of trouble!
name: "Stop That Bike!"

description: Spitfire pilot Gareth Davies, never spoke of his wartime experiences. Never spoke of how he'd been shot down over France and hunted like an animal by a remorseless Nazi killer. Never spoke of that Nazi's cold-blooded executions.But, 40 years later, a glimpse of a face across a crowded room started him talking and the whole story tumbled out.It was the story of old scores. And now was the time to settle the account!
name: Old Scores

description: By 1945, the Allies had air superiority over Germany and victory seemed inevitable.However, they were left reeling when the Luftwaffe threw in the Me262, the first-ever combat jet - a sleek, deadly killing machine nicknamed "Stormbird" by its pilots.One of those pilots was Jurgen Klose whose elder brother had been killed in the air. The young, newly-qualified pilot joined the same squadron hoping for vengeance. But when Jurgen clashed with his brutal squadron leader, it seemed there was more to Conrad's death than he originally thought...
name: Stormbird Strike!

description: They were small and mobile, the fastest craft of their respective fleets... with enough guns to pack a lethal punch. Pit them against each other at night in the mine-strewn waters between England and France and you had all the ingredients for a deadly channel clash.
name: Channel Clash

description: One Englishman, one Frenchman, one Greek, one German and one American.The French Foreign Legion had trained them to be hardened fighting men... and now they had deserted, faded out of sight.But very soon they'd be back with a bang, hiring out their deadly skills to the highest bidder. No job was too dangerous, no risk too great - not even in the heart of the Nazi Reich!
name: Hired Guns

description: Long-range guns had one disadvantage - locating their targets precisely. So the Royal Artillery employed AOPs - Air Observation Posts - slow-flying Auster aircraft that could spy out the enemy and radio their positions back to the gunners far behind their own lines.Pilot Officer Tom Harness flew one of these spotter planes, and when he was set upon by fast enemy fighters, he was to find that piloting an AOP was anything but A-okay!
name: Spy in the Sky

description: The soothsayers sing: One day, green-hued giants will clash on the broken battlefields of savage Sakaar. One day the son will confront the father who abandoned him to monsters and madmen. But before Skaar can meet the Hulk, he must survive today's terrible clash. And even with all his rage and strength, what hope can he have against the return of the SILVER SAVAGE? The Silver Surfer returns to Sakaar! Collecting SKAAR: SON OF HULK #7-12 and PLANET SKAAR PROLOGUE.
name: HC/TPB

description: They've given up everything to become Joes, their lives, their families, even their identities. They've become outlaws from their own government, but now, they must deal with something that could shatter the team forever: One among them is a TRAITOR,an agent of COBRA! Who is the spy? And will suspicion pull the Joes apart before Cobra can even take advantage? Meanwhile, a ghost from the Baroness's past comes back to haunt her...

Fan-fave Chuck Dixon takes the reins of Reloaded! Their world has been rocked by the revelation that one of their own is a traitor, a Cobra plant. Lives have been shattered, and a heart broken. Worse, Cobra is ascendant, in possession of territory that once belonged to the United States. Can things get any worse? Well, yes. Because in light of recent events, their roster is being re-shuffled, and they're being given a new squad leader, one whom they'd never expect!

A line has been drawn in the sand! Cobra has taken the Joes' field leader, Duke; their taskmaster Beach Head; and the island of Kauii! But now, a rejuvenated GI Joe is fighting back. Given a new recruit and added resources, Hawk and Co. must take back the island within 48 hours--before the United States and its allies launch a nuclear strike against it!

name: Old Scores
The Devil and the Deep Blue Sea

description: To the ancient Egyptians, Somalia was the Land of Punt, a distant country on the Horn of Africa. To "Dodgy" Turner and "Windy" Waters it was a land of sand, sweat and flies, a place where any self-respecting soldier would seek a cushy number at any price.So they volunteered to become instructors with the Somalia Camel Corps... just in time to begin a fighting retreat in the face of an overwhelming Italian attack as Punt became a land ruled by bullet, sword and fire.
name: The Land of Punt

description: In 1940 Roy Carswell, an officer cadet, was recruited straight from University into British Intelligence and sent to South America. Here he became tangled up in a deadly game against the Nazis. But how were a fabled, long lost city of the ancient Incas and his missing, presumed dead, former college professor involved?...Would Roy even survive long enough to uncover the secret of the Andes?
name: Secret of the Andes

description: After many successful missions in Korea and Malaya, the reformed Ramsey's Raiders were expecting to be returned to Civvy Street. None were pleased at the prospect.At the eleventh hour, though, they were handed one last mission. In the dense, claustrophobic heat of the Malayan jungle, they had to save one of their own - former team member Gareth "Lucky" Evans. Could the Raiders survive this latest dice with death..?
name: Raiders The Reckoning

description: In the bitter winter of 1944, Canadian Army Sergeant Billy Conroy was a POW, one of many behind the wire in a Stalag in East Prussia. That all changed after the Russian planes bombed the camp and the prisoners' German captors abandoned them to the harsh, freezing weather.Determined to survive, Billy and a couple of his fellow former inmates teamed up.But if they thought the weather was their deadliest enemy, they were wrong. To live, they'd have to fight all comers in this deadly Baltic battleground.
name: Baltic Battleground

description: Out of the night they came, guns blazing. A force of British Rolls-Royce armoured cars pouring fire at an isolated Italian outpost in the desert. The defenders were swept aside. It had been a perfect surprise attack.Now all the British had to do was get back to their own lines. With half the Italian Army after them, it might be touch and go...
name: Surprise Attack!

description: A Russian, a German and an Englishman, three men from different fighting forces, but all with one common objective, to reach the freedom of the West. It was a task fraught with danger and the promise of death in the chaos that gripped Germany in the closing stages of the war.
name: Run for Freedom

description: From the deep forests and treacherous marshes they came, a small band of Polish mercenaries led by an ex-cavalry officer and a British agent who was half-Polish himself. Their clothes were ragged, their weapons an assortment which would make any quartermaster wince.But they had one thing in common - a burning desire to fling the Nazis out of their Polish homeland. That made them as deadly and dangerous as the name they had chose for themselves - the Fighting Eagles.
name: Fighting Eagles

description: Hunter was a crack shot, a tough, well-trained sergeant. Bunter was fat and afraid - a useless soldier. From their first meeting, the two hated the sight of one another.Not the makings of a good team you'd think, but the day would come when each of them would have to depend on the other - or die!
name: Hunter and Bunter
Hero From Hollywood

description: It's a brand new era in Ben 10-ness! Witness the beginning of Ultimate Alien! New aliens! New villains! And new adventures! It all starts here!
name: Fashion Victim; Going Viral; Dodge Ben

description: Part 2 of the 4-part weekly event! The Planet's new reporter continues his interviews concerning the day Doomsday killed Superman, this time widening his subjects to the ordinary civilians who were there that day and the horrors they saw. It wasn't just Superman who died that day. Duffy also interviews the Prankster, and other lower-tier villains who tried to take credit for that day's tragedy. Meanwhile, Superman continues to investigate more mysterious accidents, as the clues to an emerging threat become clearer.
name: Superman's Death

description: Part 3 of the 4-part weekly event! Duffy interviews a priest and gets the perspective of those who must go on. How lucky do the living feel after massive tragedies? When's the next time this will happen, and will it be worse, especially after yet another massive accident occurs?
name: Funeral For A Friend

description: The conclusion of the 4-part weekly event! Duffy explores the ways we can restore hope and how we can make the best of troubled times. But that proves difficult when all hell breaks loose, the mystery of who is causing the accidents along Doomsday's path is revealed, and a deadly new threat emerges from the ashes of destruction! Will tragedy once again befall Metropolis' most famous icon on the anniversary of his death?
name: World Without A Superman

description: A prequel to this summer's most anticipated movie ! Sgt. Bosco B.A. Baracus is the kind of man you want on your side in a tough situationwhich is why he was sent into Kuwait City to help retrieve weapons stolen from the coalition during Desert Storm. But when B.A. learns that this particular mission isn't exactly what he was told, you'll pity the fool that tried to lie to him.

1. The Boy King and the Giant Featuring The Boy King

2. Checking the Checker Featuring Nightmare and Sleepy

3. The Origin of Stupid Manny Featuring Stupid Manny

4. The Origin of Micro Face Featuring Micro-Face

5. Smoke Rings of Death

6. He's a Blitz on wheels! Featuring Zippo

7. Origin of the Boy Rangers Jackie Law and the Boy Rangers

8. Murder Before the Footlights Featuring Twilight
name: The Boy King and The Giant

description:
1. A Leader Against Crime! Featuring The Boy King

2. The Upside-Down Town Featuring Nightmare and Sleepy

3. Gee - It must be rainin'..Featuring Stupid Manny

4. Crime and art are strange companions..Featuring Micro-Face

5. Detectives Have Brains

6. A Racket in Dolls Featuring Zippo

7. A Well-Laid Plot Featuring Jackie Law and the Boy Rangers

8. The Quilled Death!! Featuring Twilight
name: A Leader Against Crime!

first_appearance_teams.name: Jackie Law and the Boy Rangers

team_credits.name: Jackie Law and the Boy Rangers

description:
Throughout the South Sea Islands he was known to the natives and whites alike as 'Big Alec'. Six feet three inches of bronzed husky, Australian beach-comber, gold prospector and hunter.

Big Alec roamed the islands in tattered shirt, slacks and an old bush hat, his only companion his big game rifle, with its deadly telescopic sight.

Then came the Japs, island-hopping their way to Australia, mowing down every thing in their way - until they reached Big Alec's island.

There they stopped dead - very dead - for Big Alec never missed...
name: Sniper`s Island

description:
A handful of men alone in the desert Men nobody wanted, nobody cared about. And the mission they were on was so dangerous no one ever expected to see them alive again.

If an enemy plane didn't pick them off, the Panzers would. Either that or the burning desert would kill them in its slow, pitiless way ....

The men knew this - and they also knew the only way out was to fight like furies!.

The odds were a thousand to one - but they'd take on all the Germans in North Africa if they had to!
name: Desert Blitz

description:
Marvel's Greatest Comics - $1.00

This is a reprint of Wolverine vol.3 #66
name: Old Man Logan, Part 1

description: An all-star group of creators tackles the JSA past and present! This 8-issue miniseries provides a perfect introduction to the rich world of the JSA! The entire team is in jeopardy, and only by going off on their own can they tackle the enemy within their midst!
name: Legacy

description: Featuring a solo Hawkgirl adventure plus a Golden Age Hawkman tale by Jeph Loeb and Tim Sale! Hawkgirl takes flight to meet her grandfather, the adventurer known as Speed Saunders. And although she'll have a helluva time getting him out of his current situation, it's Kendra's past that will take the biggest toll on her, as we learn the one thing she won't share with Hawkman, or the rest of the JSA. And in the backup, the all- star team of Loeb and Sale take on the Golden Age Hawkman!
name: Flying High

description: The landmark miniseries continues! In the 16-page lead story, travel to Salem, Massachusetts, home to legends both good and evil, including Hector Hall, this generation's Doctor Fate! The DC Universe's ultimate sorcerer takes center stage as he confronts the one power of Fate he's been trying to ignore. Plus, a back-up tale of the Golden Age Doctor Fate, Kent Nelson, written and illustrated by Darwyn Cooke (CATWOMAN: SELINA'S BIG SCORE).
name: Challenging Fate

description: Spotlighting the spectacular Stargirl! The Star-Spangled Kid enlists the aid of her partner and stepfather, S.T.R.I.P.E., as she heads out on a hunt for the one person she'd rather forget: her biological father. Plus, a backup Golden Age Starman tale by the team of James Robinson & Tony Harris (STARMAN)!
name: A Star Is Born

description: Spotlighting the JSA's prophetic powerhouse Hourman! Rick Tyler has struggled to take hold of his father's legacy as the original Hourman, and after years of failure he's finally succeeded...or has he? Plus, Howard Chaykin tackles the original Hourman in a Golden Age back-up tale!
name: An Hour At A Time

description: Spotlighting Dr. Mid-Nite, featuring a Golden Age backup tale by 100 BULLETS' and BATMAN's Brian Azzarello and Eduardo Risso! What must Doctor Mid-Nite face from his past, and how will he confront the future? Plus, discover the mysterious connection between Pieter Cross and Charles McNider, the original Dr. Mid-Nite.
name: Out Of The Shadows
Tom baker

description: In this issue of Superman: The Man of Steel Annual, an alternate universe Kal-El teams up with Batman to free a Kryptonian occupied Earth. Superman begins to question Jor-El's methods when dealing with the "Terrans". He battles his own people and fights alongside them to free Earth from the rule of his own race and as usual Lex Luthor is involved.
name: Unforgiven

volume.name: Superman: The Man of Steel Annual
